          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutrons were detected in cylinders of NE",
                "102 plastic 5-in. diam. x 2-in.. thick after",
                "traversing a 106-cm flight path."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "FNB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fragment flight paths were 125 and 99 cm.",
                "The neutron beam was filtered through 6 in of bismuth",
                "and 8 in of quartz to give a thermal neutron flux of",
                "2 x 108 n/cm2 s. The efficiency of the neutron",
                "detectors was obtained by comparing the observed",
                "time-of-flight spectrum in each of the counter with",
                "the accurately known 235U neutron spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "After a preliminary inspection, the neutron",
                "time-of-flight spectrum is divided into four regions:",
                "background, gamma, neutron and background. In the",
                "first pass fission fragments associated with the two",
                "background regions are sorted to determine the",
                "\"normal\" distribution, i.e. number of fissions as a",
                "function of mass and energy without reference to",
                "neutron emission. On the second pass, gamma events",
                "are sorted and a Gaussian fitted to the peak to",
                "obtain the zero of the neutron time scale. On the",
                "third pass, events in the two background regions are",
                "folded into the neutron region in such a way that",
                "there is a one-to-one correspondence between a",
                "channel in the neutron region and one in the",
                "background region. The treatment of the neutron",
                "region in the fourth pass is identical to described",
                "above, except for the sign of the weights and the",
                "conversion of the channel numbers. In addition to the",
                "momentum information for all fragment masses and",
                "energies, the computer also stores the complete",
                "velocity spectrum for the two major fragment groups,",
                "light and heavy."
              ]
            }
          ],
